Employees of China Eastern Airlines, wearing augmented reality (AR) glasses, welcome important guests at Beijing Daxing International Airport's VIP room on Thursday. The AR glasses can capture individuals' facial information and compare it with passenger information to see if a person is permitted to enter certain places, such as VIP rooms, and their corresponding flight details. Photo: Li Xuanmin/GT
